00:21:40,510 --> 00:21:41,350
Mr. Xu.

411
00:21:50,270 --> 00:21:51,110
Mr. Zheng.

412
00:21:55,360 --> 00:21:56,200
Sorry,

413
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:58,810
I disappointed you.

414
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:11,230
The streets are packed.

415
00:22:11,710 --> 00:22:13,360
It's the Dragon Boat Festival.

416
00:22:17,030 --> 00:22:18,030
Earlier today,

417
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:19,600
I went to see Lord Wei.

418
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:22,470
So did I.

419
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:31,520
Mr. Xu,

420
00:22:32,310 --> 00:22:33,200
how about

421
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:35,990
we eat plain noodles? My treat.

422
00:22:35,990 --> 00:22:38,460
(Noodles)

423
00:22:39,510 --> 00:22:40,350
Mr. Zheng,

424
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:41,960
I'm not hungry.

425
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:44,120
I am.

426
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:54,790
- Enjoy.
- This is a specialty of Jiangnan.

427
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:56,310
It's been my favorite since childhood.

428
00:22:56,310 --> 00:22:57,310
Taste it.

429
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,200
Earlier today,

430
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:09,160
I went to the Six Ministries
and other offices.

431
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:11,790
Thankfully, Lord Wei let me in.

432
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:15,160
Or I'd be even more embarrassed.

433
00:23:18,070 --> 00:23:19,960
The officials are waiting.

434
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:23,640
I understand.

435
00:23:25,030 --> 00:23:25,870
Mr. Zheng,

436
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:30,030
what are you going to do next?

437
00:23:30,470 --> 00:23:31,960
What do you suggest?

438
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:35,960
There's a well-known tale

439
00:23:36,160 --> 00:23:37,360
in my hometown

440
00:23:37,550 --> 00:23:39,440
called The Tortoise and the Hare.

441
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:41,200
I'd like to tell you about it.

442
00:23:41,510 --> 00:23:42,350
Go ahead.

443
00:23:43,710 --> 00:23:45,710
The Tortoise and the Hare are racing.

444
00:23:46,070 --> 00:23:47,400
The Hare is faster,

445
00:23:47,550 --> 00:23:49,710
leaving the Tortoise far behind.

446
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:51,310
The Hare is

447
00:23:51,310 --> 00:23:52,790
proud of its speed,

448
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:54,070
thinking it'll win for sure

449
00:23:54,510 --> 00:23:56,920
and going to nap halfway.

450
00:23:57,750 --> 00:23:58,920
Meanwhile, the Tortoise

451
00:23:59,550 --> 00:24:02,600
keeps crawling and crawling,

452
00:24:02,990 --> 00:24:05,440
crawling and crawling.

453
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:07,470
It hasn't stopped at all.

454
00:24:08,230 --> 00:24:10,270
By the time the Hare wakes up,

455
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:12,510
the Tortoise has reached the finishing line.

456
00:24:14,550 --> 00:24:16,030
As slow as it is,

457
00:24:16,230 --> 00:24:17,600
it'll get there eventually.

458
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,880
Why not consider Lord Wei's advice

459
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:23,270
to think about those three things?

460
00:24:24,120 --> 00:24:25,310
Take a step back

461
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:26,920
and take things slow.

462
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,240
Mr. Xu,

463
00:24:31,550 --> 00:24:34,550
I'm going to tell you a story, too.

464
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:36,390
Please.

465
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,880
Many years ago, a scholar

466
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:44,270
became an official at a young age.

467
00:24:45,310 --> 00:24:47,400
He was full of political ambition.

468
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:48,750
At the age of 30,

469
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,310
he went to Chuzhou.

470
00:24:51,310 --> 00:24:52,880
Everyone thought

471
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:56,120
he volunteered to serve the people there,

472
00:24:56,840 --> 00:24:57,960
but actually,

473
00:24:58,470 --> 00:25:00,990
he was exiled to that remote barren land

474
00:25:01,310 --> 00:25:04,120
for offending the then Prime Minister.

475
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:05,750
At first,

476
00:25:05,990 --> 00:25:07,680
he hated that place.

477
00:25:08,270 --> 00:25:09,680
That exiled official

478
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:11,030
was frustrated.

479
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,600
He was eager to make achievements

480
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:16,440
to return to the capital someday.

481
00:25:16,710 --> 00:25:19,160
Why didn't he go back to the capital?

482
00:25:26,310 --> 00:25:28,920
In the beginning, he put his career first.

483
00:25:30,230 --> 00:25:31,270
Later,

484
00:25:31,710 --> 00:25:34,880
he saw how poor the locals were,

485
00:25:36,270 --> 00:25:37,550
but he also saw

486
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:40,680
their kindness

487
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:43,400
and vitality.

488
00:25:45,550 --> 00:25:47,440
He loved to go to one street.

489
00:25:47,990 --> 00:25:51,750
Originally, he went there
only to eat plain noodles.

490
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:54,680
Then

491
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:59,360
he found the coarse buns
sold in the shop on the street corner

492
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:01,270
also flavorful.

493
00:26:03,070 --> 00:26:06,440
He saw the widow on the west side

494
00:26:07,070 --> 00:26:08,640
marry another man

495
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:14,640
and a boy with snot
playing games on the street corner

496
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:16,200
grow up

497
00:26:17,360 --> 00:26:19,960
and help his father run the lamb stall.

498
00:26:23,710 --> 00:26:25,200
In 20 years' time,

499
00:26:26,470 --> 00:26:28,710
he got to know many people there

500
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,600
and walked down every street.

501
00:26:34,120 --> 00:26:36,030
That city wasn't as beautiful as Jiangnan

502
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:38,400
or as bustling as the capital,

503
00:26:39,270 --> 00:26:40,710
but as time passed,

504
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:43,640
it became his hometown.

505
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:45,840
He decided

506
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:47,400
to stay.

507
00:26:51,600 --> 00:26:53,230
Is the scholar in that story

508
00:26:54,200 --> 00:26:55,120
you, sir?

509
00:27:01,310 --> 00:27:03,200
I'm over 50 years old.

510
00:27:03,790 --> 00:27:05,440
I should know the mandate of heaven.

511
00:27:06,550 --> 00:27:08,440
I became unambitious a long time ago.

512
00:27:09,310 --> 00:27:11,880
I just wanted to look after my mother,

513
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:13,270
children, and grandchildren

514
00:27:13,710 --> 00:27:15,880
while keeping Chuzhou safe.

515
00:27:21,200 --> 00:27:22,920
But the city was destroyed

516
00:27:24,750 --> 00:27:26,710
overnight.

517
00:27:28,230 --> 00:27:29,360
All those people

518
00:27:31,160 --> 00:27:32,680
ended up dead.

519
00:27:48,070 --> 00:27:51,030
I wanted to live a carefree life.

520
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:53,990
I wanted to take things slow.

521
00:27:56,070 --> 00:27:57,600
But the deceased

522
00:27:58,880 --> 00:28:01,790
came to haunt me every single night.

523
00:28:04,840 --> 00:28:06,120
I couldn't live

524
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:08,270
or die.

525
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:10,440
I couldn't give in

526
00:28:11,550 --> 00:28:13,200
or give up.

527
00:28:14,990 --> 00:28:16,360
Bones piled up.

528
00:28:16,750 --> 00:28:18,470
I saw them all the time.

529
00:28:19,160 --> 00:28:21,070
Their wail was echoing.

530
00:28:34,750 --> 00:28:36,750
Lord Wei said to take things slow.

531
00:28:37,790 --> 00:28:39,360
He might be right,

532
00:28:40,750 --> 00:28:41,840
but I...

533
00:28:45,120 --> 00:28:46,790
cannot stop.

534
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:11,790
Sir, would you like some water lanterns?

535
00:29:12,030 --> 00:29:13,550
Float them with your wishes

536
00:29:13,550 --> 00:29:15,400
to pray for heaven's blessing

537
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:16,840
and your wishes to come true.

538
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:27,510
I'd like one.

539
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:35,520
Here you go.

540
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:37,440
Thank you, sir!

541
00:29:57,840 --> 00:29:58,680
Mr. Zheng,

542
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:06,470
may your wishes come true.

543
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:13,750
I hope so.

544
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:22,990
What's going on in the Cabinet lately?

545
00:30:23,230 --> 00:30:24,270
Your Majesty,

546
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:26,750
Prime Minister Wang didn't see anyone.

547
00:30:30,030 --> 00:30:30,920
What about Wei Yuan?

548
00:30:31,750 --> 00:30:33,310
Two days ago, after the court meeting,

549
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:36,840
Commissioner Zheng
went to the Guardian Yamen.

550
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:39,030
Lord Wei received him.

551
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:41,070
Since then,

552
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:43,400
they haven't crossed paths again.

553
00:30:44,790 --> 00:30:46,470
Both of them are smart.

554
00:30:47,030 --> 00:30:48,550
Rejecting Zheng Xinghuai

555
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:51,160
is to give him a way out.

556
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:53,470
But

557
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:55,030
Wei Yuan

558
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:57,880
respects me even less.

559
00:30:59,270 --> 00:31:00,400
What did Zheng Xinghuai do?

560
00:31:00,990 --> 00:31:01,920
Your Majesty,

561
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:04,750
he didn't take Lord Wei's advice.

562
00:31:05,680 --> 00:31:08,400
He's been running around

563
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:10,200
to incite the high-ups

564
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:11,510
and persuade the officials.

565
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:14,360
But they won't see him.

566
00:31:14,510 --> 00:31:15,640
They know

567
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:17,640
what you're thinking.

568
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:24,640
He's digging his own grave.

569
00:31:32,120 --> 00:31:33,160
Who are you?

570
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:35,720
Step back.

571
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,160
I am

572
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:48,470
the Commander of Chuzhou,

573
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,790
State Duke of Protection, Que Yongxiu!

574
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:52,960
I'm here to sue

575
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:57,600
the Commissioner of Chuzhou,
Zheng Xinghuai!

576
00:31:57,790 --> 00:31:59,750
He murdered Duke Zhenbei!

577
00:32:00,510 --> 00:32:05,310
He killed 380,000 people of Chuzhou!

